      "author_association": "MEMBER",
      "body": "Yes, thanks for the report.  I also agree the `-reindex-chainstate help text seems quite clear to me on this:\n\n```cpp\nargsman.AddArg(\"-reindex-chainstate\", \"If enabled, wipe chain state, and rebuild it from blk*.dat files on disk. If an assumeutxo snapshot was loaded, its chainstate will be wiped as well. The snapshot can then be reloaded via RPC.\", ArgsManager::ALLOW_ANY, OptionsCategory::OPTIONS);\n```\n\nIt seems that there is little interest (or need) for the project to do anything actionable here, therefore I'm going to close this issue.",
